    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "Wallet: add consistency check on wallet transactions stored on wallet database when loading the wallet.",
    "user": {
      "login": "Luquitasjeffrey",
      "id": 105951354,
      "node_id": "U_kgDOBlCweg",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/105951354?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Luquitasjeffrey",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/Luquitasjeffrey",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Luquitasjeffrey/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Luquitasjeffrey/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Luquitasjeffrey/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Luquitasjeffrey/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Luquitasjeffrey/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Luquitasjeffrey/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Luquitasjeffrey/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Luquitasjeffrey/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Luquitasjeffrey/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "Fixes: #34599 \r\nWhen loading a corrupted wallet database there exists the chance where the transaction state is inconsistent. For example, in the wallet database a parent transaction could appear to be inactive while the child transaction was confirmed (of course that makes no sense, in the blockchain both transactions are confirmed). As a result, when the wallet attempts to abandon inactive transactions, it raises an assertion error. \r\nTo fix the problem, if when loading the wallet it encounters an inconsistent transaction state, it will return NEED_RESCAN as db errors, because, it is not usable a wallet that has inconsistent transaction state.\r\n\r\n* Adds a new test case in wallet_tests.cpp: test_crash_corrupt_wallet_abandon\r\n",
