      "body": "Question: Should these assignments preserve any more severe load error already stored in `result`?\n\nSince `DBErrors` is severity-ordered, and this function already tracks the worst result via `std::max`, a plain assignment to `DBErrors::NEED_RESCAN` could silently overwrite a more severe error already stored in `result`. Would `result = std::max(result, DBErrors::NEED_RESCAN)` be safer here?",
